cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper introduces a method to improve deep learning models, specifically addressing the overfitting problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the performance of residual networks, which are commonly used in image classification tasks, further supporting the likelihood of cs.CV. The use of stochastic affine combinations also suggests a potential connection to Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which could also be relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
